nif_0000_03208_2.name: Analysis of the androgen receptor (AR) and R1881-regulated transcriptomes in LNCaP cells
nif_0000_03208_2.description: (1) Human LNCaP prostatic carcinoma cells at late passage were treated with or without 1 nM R1881 for 6 h. (2) Human LNCaP prostatic carcinoma cells were infected with AR shRNA lentivirus or non-target control lentivirus.
nif_0000_03208_2.tissue_cell_lines: Male reproductive, prostate, epithelium, LNCaP-LP50 cells
nif_0000_03208_2.contributors: Trumbly RJ,  Gonit M,  Zhang J,  d’Alincourt Salazara M,  Cui H,  Shatnawi A,  Trumbly R,  Ratnam M

nif_0000_03208_2.name: Transcriptomic analysis of all-trans retinoic acid (ATRA)-and 16-keto-estradiol (16KE2) treated human acute promyelocytic cells
nif_0000_03208_2.description: Acute promyelocytic cells were isolated from leukopharesis samples from a patient with acute promyelocytic leukemia (APL) who had a t(15;17) and a white blood cell count of 185,000 with 97% myeloblasts at diagnosis. Cells were treated for 5 days with or without (1) 1 µM ATRA; or (2) 70 µM 16KE2.
nif_0000_03208_2.contributors: Ross K,  Stegmaier K,  Ross KN,  Colavito SA,  O'Malley S,  Stockwell BR,  Golub TR,  O’Malley S

nif_0000_03208_2.name: Analysis of the testosterone (Test)-regulated transcriptome in female mouse liver
nif_0000_03208_2.description: Livers were isolated from 10-12 week old female C57BL/6 mice treated with or without (1) bi-weekly doses of 0.9 mg Test for 3 weeks; or (2) bi-weekly doses of 0.9 mg Test for 3 weeks followed by discontinuation of Test and vehicle treatments for 12 weeks.  The dose of Test used has been shown to raise the circulating Test concentration in female mice to a level normally found in male mice.
nif_0000_03208_2.contributors: Krücken J,  Delić D,  Weiland C,  Vohr H,  Wunderlich F

nif_0000_03208_2.name: Analysis of the oxidative stress-dependent transcriptome in mouse bone marrow-derived macrophages
nif_0000_03208_2.description: Bone marrow derived macrophages from C57Bl/6 mice were treated for 4 h with or without (i) lipopolysaccharide; (ii) oxidative stress-derived extracellular vesicles (stressEVs); or (iii) stressEVs that had undergone the Fenton reaction (stressEVs-FR).
nif_0000_03208_2.contributors: Horvat S,  Manček-Keber M,  Frank M,  Hafner-Bratkovič I,  Smole A,  Zorko M,  Pirher N,  Hayer S,  Kralj-Iglič V,  Rozman B,  Ilc N,  Jerala R
